The article discusses the upcoming National Lab Day, a grassroots effort to improve science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) education in the United States. The event is in response to President Obama's call to elevate STEM education as a national priority. Cabinet secretaries and senior administration officials, along with teachers and volunteers, are scheduled to participate in hands-on learning activities with students. The article also mentions the financial support and partnerships that National Lab Day has received, as well as the various projects and connections it has created. Additionally, the MacArthur Foundation will announce the winners of its "21st Century Learning Lab Designers" competition during the event. National Lab Day has projects in every state, as well as Puerto Rico, Guam, and the US Virgin Islands.